{"id":1776,"date":"2015-06-28T11:45:23","date_gmt":"2015-06-28T08:45:23","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/?p=1776"},"modified":"2015-06-28T11:45:23","modified_gmt":"2015-06-28T08:45:23","slug":"ramadan-2015-1436h-food-distribution","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/ramadan-2015-1436h-food-distribution\/","title":{"rendered":"Ramadan 2015 (1436H) &#8211; Food Distribution"},"content":{"rendered":"<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span class=\"s1\"><a href=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/All-3.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-1777\" src=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/All-3-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"All 3\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/All-3-225x300.jpg 225w, https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/All-3.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 225px) 100vw, 225px\" \/><\/a>Qidwai Welfare Trust had\u00a0a very successful 2015 Ramadan<\/span> <span class=\"s1\">Food Distribution, where we distributed from June 16 &#8211; June 21 approximately<\/span> <span class=\"s1\">71,250kg (157,300 lb) of food\u00a0stables to 1,350\u00a0Zakat eligible families, and arranged to<\/span> <span class=\"s1\">have\u00a0375 orphans and student to be fed during the month of Ramadan.<\/span><\/p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">Each family received a food pack with approximately 50kg (110 lb) of food stables, including 20kg of flour, 10kg of rice, 5kg of sugar, 5kg of oil, 4kg of lentils,\u00a02kg of chickpeas, 2kg of gram flour, 1kg of dates, 0.5kg of tea, 0.5 kg of salt, 2 bottles\u00a0of concentrated juice and\u00a0mix\u00a0spices.<\/p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span class=\"s1\">We distributed 270 food packs in Burma Town \u2013 Punjab, 100 food packs in Tarnol \u2013 Punjab, 30 food packs in Islamabad, 200 food packs in Mansehra \u2013 KPK, 50 food packs in Upper Dir KPK, 200 food packs in Bagh \u2013 Azzad Jammu Kashmir, 200 food packs in Lahore \u2013 Punjab, 200 food packs in Tharparkar\u00a0\u2013\u00a0Sindh, 100 food packs in Karachi \u2013 Sindh.<\/span><\/p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span class=\"s1\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-1675\" src=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/DSC_05411-300x199.jpg\" alt=\"DSC_0541\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" srcset=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/DSC_05411-300x199.jpg 300w, https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/DSC_05411-1024x680.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/DSC_05411.jpg 1126w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/>All the families\/recipients were pre-screened by our partner organizations, (Muslim Aid Pakistan, Almustafa Development Network, and Help Change a Life), \u00a0a couple of days prior to the distribution and all efforts were made to ensure they were Zakat eligible. <\/span>Preference was given to poor and needy families of orphans, widows and disabled people.<\/p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span class=\"s1\">The distribution was also facilitated by a team of\u00a0\u00a0older boys and foster couples from our\u00a0Orphan Homes. This was done\u00a0to help build our own capacity and to get the older children involved in charity and welfare activities.<\/span><\/p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span class=\"s1\">By the grace of Allah, this was the eighth\u00a0consecutive year Qidwai Welfare Trust organized its annual Ramadan Food Distribution.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/Burma-Town.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1522\" src=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/Burma-Town.jpg\" alt=\"Burma Town\" width=\"600\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/Burma-Town.jpg 600w, https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/Burma-Town-225x300.jpg 225w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/Tarnol-A.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1523\" src=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/Tarnol-A.jpg\" alt=\"Tarnol A\" width=\"600\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/Tarnol-A.jpg 600w, https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/Tarnol-A-225x300.jpg 225w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/Mansehra.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1528\" src=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/Mansehra.jpg\" alt=\"Mansehra\" width=\"600\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/Mansehra.jpg 600w, https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/Mansehra-225x300.jpg 225w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/Bagh.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1532\" src=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/Bagh.jpg\" alt=\"Bagh\" width=\"600\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/Bagh.jpg 600w, https:\/\/qidwaiw